Package userinterface

Class DocumentCellDecorator

java.lang.Object
userinterface.AbstractFrame
userinterface.DocumentCell
userinterface.DocumentCellDecorator
Direct Known Subclasses:
HorizontalScrollBarDecorator, VerticalScrollBarDecorator
public abstract class DocumentCellDecorator
extends DocumentCell
A class of decorators that decorate a visualization of a DocumentCell in browsr with a scroll bar.

    • handleResize

      public void handleResize​(int newWindowWidth, int newWindowHeight)
      This method handles resizes. It makes sure the Frame is adjusted in width when the window shrinks or grows. It does not change its height (e.g. look at Firefox).

      N.B.: without this method, BookmarksBar would be rendered with the given absolute width, and thus one would need to guess the correct initial size of the window. Using this method, widths are automatically adjusted: both at initialization and at runtime.

      Overrides:
      handleResize in class DocumentCell
      Parameters:
      newWindowWidth - : parameter containing the new window-width of this Frame.
      newWindowHeight - : parameter containing the new window-height of this Frame.
